# Chat SDK fit/gap

## Verdict

**Use Chat SDK as the platform adapter layer. Do not call it a gateway replacement, and do not cut inbound over yet.** It covers the expensive platform mechanics we want to stop hand-rolling: Discord/Telegram/Slack sends, DMs, inbound messages, reactions, commands, thread handles, rich cards, and cross-platform handler shapes. The source also has central self-message filtering, dedupe, and per-thread/channel concurrency strategies. ([core inbound path](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2455), [common handler surface](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L515-L864))

**It does not replace the semantics that make the joelclaw gateway safe.** Sender authorization, Telegram outbound policy, durable priority dispatch, batching/supersession/replay, exact message journaling, delivery audits, channel health/healing, and bounded error emission remain joelclaw wrappers around the SDK. ([current Discord allowlist](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/discord.ts#L186-L203), [current Telegram allowlist](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/telegram.ts#L1080-L1099), [current durable queue](../../../packages/gateway/src/command-queue.ts#L520-L711), [current journal](../../../packages/gateway/src/message-journal.ts#L53-L149))

**“Stabilize on this” is not true yet.** All three adapter docs explicitly mark themselves `beta: true`; the repository shipped four synchronized version trains between June 16 and July 13, and recent releases fixed previously silent message loss, broken concurrency caps, and Telegram send rejection. Pin an exact version, wrap it, and shadow it. Do not let a fast-moving public beta become the new nervous-system single point of failure. ([Discord beta marker](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/discord.mdx#L1-L10), [Telegram beta marker](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/telegram.mdx#L1-L10), [Slack beta marker](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/slack.mdx#L1-L10), [4.33 retry-loss fix](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/CHANGELOG.md#L69-L78), [4.27 concurrency fix](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/CHANGELOG.md#L181-L219))

## Source snapshot and confidence

This report inspected `vercel/chat` at commit [`80def3a`](https://github.com/vercel/chat/commit/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191), three adapter implementations and tests, the core `Chat`/`Thread` types, first-party adapter docs, package changelogs, releases, and the local gateway source. Published package manifests were `4.34.0`; `main` was three days newer than that tag, so source-level claims below are pinned to the commit rather than to floating `main`. ([core package manifest](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/package.json#L1-L13), [4.34 release](https://github.com/vercel/chat/releases/tag/chat%404.34.0))

Live readback on 2026-07-16 (`joelclaw gateway status`) showed Telegram configured/healthy on polling, Slack configured/healthy with Socket Mode connected, and Discord disabled. That confirms the Telegram and Slack identities/transports are live without exposing credentials; it also confirms Discord reuse is a provisioning/config task, not a current-live-channel claim. (`command: joelclaw gateway status`, `file:/Users/joel/.joelclaw/scripts/gateway-start.sh:73-89`)

Legend: **Yes** means source implements the capability. **Partial** means the SDK exposes it but the platform/model loses semantics. **Wrapper** means Chat SDK supplies mechanics but joelclaw must retain policy or durability.

## The valuable “Chat SDK cannot do X” list

1. **It cannot authorize Joel.** Chat SDK skips messages from the bot itself, but it has no configured sender allowlist or joelclaw role/reply-grant policy. Today Discord and Telegram drop any sender whose ID is not Joel’s, while Slack distinguishes Joel DMs, mentions, important-channel passive intel, and Reply Grants. Keep that policy before any SDK event reaches the dispatcher. ([core self filter only](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2067), [Discord allowlist](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/discord.ts#L186-L203), [Telegram allowlist](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/telegram.ts#L1080-L1099), [Slack routing policy](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/slack.ts#L710-L897))
2. **It cannot replace `command-queue`.** Its `drop | queue | debounce | burst | concurrent` strategies serialize message handlers, but they do not provide joelclaw’s Redis priority queue, durable ack/replay, pending batches, active-turn supersession/abort, passive-intel path, or context-overflow recovery. ([SDK concurrency contract](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/types.ts#L54-L150), [SDK queue implementation](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2100-L2455), [joelclaw persistence/supersession](../../../packages/gateway/src/command-queue.ts#L520-L711), [joelclaw drain/recovery](../../../packages/gateway/src/command-queue.ts#L858-L1228))
3. **It cannot issue an honest joelclaw delivery receipt.** A send returns a platform message ID/raw response and methods for edit/delete/reaction; it has no `flowId`, producer, route, requested/confirmed timestamps, suppression state, delivery state, or fail-open outbox. Keep contract-v2 envelopes and journal the returned SDK message ID. ([SDK sent-message shape](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/types.ts#L1468-L1513), [joelclaw journal fail-open path](../../../packages/gateway/src/message-journal.ts#L53-L149), [current outbound envelope](../../../packages/gateway/src/outbound/envelope.ts#L1-L25))
4. **It cannot enforce Telegram signal policy.** There is no equivalent of deliver/digest/suppress/investigate, trusted-conversation exemptions, specialized-UI exemptions, or the signal lifecycle actor. Run `routeTelegramOutbound` before `thread.post()`. ([Telegram policy](../../../packages/gateway/src/telegram-outbound-policy.ts#L1-L344))
5. **It cannot supervise channel health.** Adapters log and expose some lifecycle methods, but there is no unified healthy/degraded/disabled snapshot, mute policy, transition alert, restart threshold, cooldown, or verified heal attempt. Keep `channel-health` and adapt SDK lifecycle signals into it. ([joelclaw health model](../../../packages/gateway/src/channel-health.ts#L1-L390), [Slack SDK disconnect](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L1902-L2220))
6. **It cannot bound repetitive operator errors.** Chat SDK has a logger; it has no distinct-error budget or window summary. Keep `ErrorEmissionBudget` around Redis/channel error publication. ([error budget](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/error-emission-budget.ts#L1-L118), [current Redis use](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/redis.ts#L18-L137))
7. **It cannot offer one unambiguous `openDM(userId)` when Discord and Telegram are both installed.** Both platforms use numeric IDs; core deliberately throws `AMBIGUOUS_USER_ID` when more than one numeric adapter is registered. Contract v2 must carry the platform and call that adapter’s `openDM`, then obtain a `Chat.thread()` handle. ([numeric-ID ambiguity](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L1900-L1970))
8. **It cannot create a new Telegram relationship.** Telegram bots cannot start a conversation; Joel must already have messaged or added the bot. The adapter’s `openDM` merely encodes the supplied chat ID. ([Telegram platform rule](https://core.telegram.org/bots), [adapter `openDM`](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L1575-L1605))
9. **It cannot safely run a second shadow ingress listener beside every current listener.** Telegram long polling is a single-consumer path and webhooks/polling are mutually exclusive; Slack may distribute Socket Mode payloads across multiple open connections rather than duplicate them. Shadow normalized events inside the existing process, or transfer transport ownership explicitly. ([Telegram runtime modes](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L330-L586), [Slack multiple-connection behavior](https://docs.slack.dev/apis/events-api/using-socket-mode/), [current Telegram lease warning](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/telegram.ts#L1798-L1810))
10. **It cannot shut down every persistent adapter through `Chat.shutdown()`.** Core only calls optional `adapter.disconnect`; Slack implements it, but Telegram exposes `stopPolling()` instead and Discord’s duration-bound listener destroys its private client only when that duration ends. The LaunchAgent wrapper must own Telegram stop and Discord listener abort/restart. ([core shutdown](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L456-L484), [Telegram stop](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L459-L515), [Discord duration lifecycle](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L1961-L2108))

## Discord fit/gap

| Capability | Fit | Reality and receipt |
|---|---|---|
| Outbound DM | **Yes, adapter-specific** | `openDM(userId)` calls Discord’s `/users/@me/channels` and returns a `discord:@me:<channel>` thread ID. In the three-adapter process, call `discord.openDM()` rather than ambiguous core `chat.openDM(numericId)`. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L1728-L1760)) |
| Proactive send | **Yes** | A known DM/thread ID can be turned into a `Chat.thread()` outside webhook context, and `postMessage` calls the channel message API directly. No inbound request context is required. ([thread handle](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L1839-L1898), [post](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L1134-L1195)) |
| Reactions in | **Yes, Gateway required** | Gateway add/remove events become `ReactionEvent`; HTTP Interactions alone do not receive regular messages or reactions. ([reaction source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L924-L1008), [transport split](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/README.md#architecture-http-interactions-vs-gateway)) |
| Threads | **Yes, native** | Incoming mentions outside a thread create a Discord thread; messages in native public/private threads retain parent + thread IDs. DMs remain DM channels. ([forwarded message path](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L803-L923), [thread creation](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L1271-L1322)) |
| Cards/buttons | **Strong partial** | Embeds are default; opt-in Components v2 supports containers, sections, text displays, media galleries, buttons, and string selects. Discord modals are not implemented. ([adapter docs](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/discord.mdx#L11-L45), [payload builder](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L1009-L1133)) |
| Commands/interactions | **Yes, handling only** | Slash commands and component clicks work through signed HTTP Interactions or through Gateway-only mode. Discord delivers interactions through one configured path, not both. The adapter handles commands but does not replace current command registration/provisioning. ([webhook dispatch](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L226-L328), [Gateway interaction path](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L2109-L2252), [current registration](../../../packages/gateway/src/discord-ui/slash-commands/register.ts#L1-L109)) |
| Mentions | **Yes** | Direct bot mentions and configured role mentions route; `@everyone/@here` is ignored by default unless explicitly enabled. Regular message/mention events need the Gateway. ([mention source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L803-L923), [4.34 behavior](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/CHANGELOG.md#L1-L17)) |
| Self-message filtering | **Yes, but keep allowlist** | Constructor sets `botUserId = applicationId`; direct Gateway mode drops all bot authors, while forwarded mode marks `isMe` and relies on core’s self filter. This blocks self-wake loops but not unauthorized humans. ([identity](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L114-L198), [direct filter](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L2109-L2140), [core filter](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2067)) |
| Concurrency | **Core only** | The common state-backed strategy applies after adapter normalization. It is not a Discord transport queue and does not replace active-turn supersession. ([core](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2455)) |
| Streaming | **Fallback only** | Discord uses the SDK’s post-and-edit fallback, not a native stream API. ([feature table](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/discord.mdx#L11-L18), [Thread fallback](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/thread.ts#L598-L861)) |

## Telegram fit/gap

| Capability | Fit | Reality and receipt |
|---|---|---|
| Outbound DM | **Partial** | `openDM(userId)` only encodes `telegram:<chatId>`; it does not open a platform conversation. It works for Joel’s existing chat because Joel has already contacted the bot. ([adapter source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L1575-L1605), [platform rule](https://core.telegram.org/bots)) |
| Proactive send | **Yes for a known reachable chat** | `postMessage` calls Bot API methods with the encoded `chat_id`, independent of inbound webhook context. Contract v2 must carry `platform: telegram` because numeric IDs are ambiguous in core `openDM`. ([send source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L859-L1034), [ambiguity](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L1900-L1970)) |
| Reactions in | **Yes** | `message_reaction` updates are diffed into add/remove events with normalized emoji and actor identity. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L791-L858)) |
| Threads | **Partial** | The adapter preserves Telegram `message_thread_id` for forum topics. Ordinary private replies are still one chat-level conversation, and server history is only an adapter/process cache unless Chat thread history is persisted in a state adapter. ([ID model](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L1575-L1639), [cached history](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L1484-L1574)) |
| Cards/buttons | **Partial** | Cards become MarkdownV2 fallback text plus inline callback/link keyboards. No select menus, card images, modals, or ephemeral messages. ([feature table](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/telegram.mdx#L11-L48), [callback handling](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L744-L790)) |
| Commands/interactions | **Yes at 4.31+** | Source parses Telegram `bot_command` entities and dispatches core slash handlers; callback queries dispatch actions. The package README’s older “Slash commands: No” row is stale; source and current docs frontmatter say yes. ([command source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L635-L743), [4.31 release](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/CHANGELOG.md#L39-L49), [current docs](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/telegram.mdx#L25-L48)) |
| Mentions | **Yes** | It checks mention/text-mention/command entities and a username regex; 4.34 fixed false positives such as `@bot` matching `@bot-dev`. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L2476-L2528), [fix](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/CHANGELOG.md#L1-L13)) |
| Self-message filtering | **Yes when identity resolves** | Initialization calls `getMe`, `toAuthor` compares sender ID with the bot ID, and core drops `isMe`. If `getMe` fails, initialization warns and continues without `_botUserId`; keep the outer Joel allowlist rather than treating this as authorization. ([initialize](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L330-L376), [author mapping](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L2434-L2467), [core filter](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2067)) |
| Concurrency | **Core, channel-scoped** | Telegram sets `lockScope = "channel"`, so forum topics/private messages in one chat contend on the same lock. Choose queue/burst deliberately; default `drop` would be a semantic regression from joelclaw’s durable queue. ([adapter scope](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L248-L278), [default drop](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L291-L380)) |
| Streaming | **Partial** | Private chats use rich draft previews when supported; non-DM or unsupported paths fall back to post/edit. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L1233-L1483), [feature table](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/telegram.mdx#L11-L18)) |

## Slack fit/gap

| Capability | Fit | Reality and receipt |
|---|---|---|
| Outbound DM | **Yes** | `openDM(userId)` calls `conversations.open` and returns a conversation-scoped Slack thread handle. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L4538-L4570)) |
| Proactive send | **Yes, with auth context caveat** | Single-workspace bot tokens work outside webhooks. Multi-workspace deployments must resolve an installation and wrap work in `withBotToken`; joelclaw is single-workspace today. ([adapter docs](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/README.md#using-the-adapter-outside-webhooks), [token resolution](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L810-L870)) |
| Reactions in | **Yes** | `reaction_added`/`reaction_removed` resolve the parent thread, normalize emoji, resolve the actor, and dispatch core reaction handlers. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L2408-L2499)) |
| Threads | **Yes, native with DM wrinkle** | Channels use native `thread_ts`. Under Slack `agent_view`, each top-level DM is a thread root; the adapter bridges subscribed conversation-scoped `openDM()` handles back to incoming DMs. Transcript history is safer than channel history because threaded bot replies do not appear in top-level DM history. ([routing source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L2222-L2346), [DM history warning](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/slack.mdx#L273-L293)) |
| Cards/buttons | **Strongest** | Cards become Block Kit; buttons, links, selects, tables, charts, modals, and ephemeral messages are implemented. ([feature table](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/slack.mdx#L11-L53), [card send](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L3424-L3542), [modal handlers](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L1751-L1901)) |
| Commands/interactions | **Yes** | Webhook and Socket Mode both route slash commands, block actions, dynamic options, modal submissions, and modal closes. ([webhook dispatch](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L1249-L1654), [socket dispatch](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L1944-L2028)) |
| Mentions | **Yes** | `app_mention` and normal message events share the normalized path; inline mention conversion resolves Slack user IDs/display names. ([event routing](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L1413-L1485), [mention resolution](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L2851-L2947)) |
| Self-message filtering | **Yes when bot identity resolves** | Slack compares both bot user ID and bot ID, including per-request multi-workspace identity, then core drops `isMe`. `auth.test` failure only warns in single-workspace initialization, so outer authorization and health checks still matter. ([identity init](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L835-L870), [self check](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L5248-L5267), [core filter](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2067)) |
| Concurrency | **Core only** | State-backed core strategies apply to normalized Slack events. They do not know joelclaw priority, passive intel, Reply Grants, or active Pi turn cancellation. ([core](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2455), [current Slack policy](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/slack.ts#L710-L1016)) |
| Streaming | **Yes, conditional native** | Native Slack streaming requires a DM/thread recipient context and suitable app features/scopes; unsupported workspaces fall back to throttled post/edit, and structured chunks are dropped in fallback mode. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L4227-L4537), [4.34 hardening](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/CHANGELOG.md#L20-L67)) |

## Inbound dispatcher reality

Chat SDK can normalize `onDirectMessage`, `onNewMention`, `onNewMessage`, `onSubscribedMessage`, `onReaction`, `onAction`, and `onSlashCommand` across the three adapters. It centrally deduplicates message IDs, filters `author.isMe`, and applies state-backed locks/queues after normalization. ([handler registration](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L515-L864), [inbound pipeline](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2455))

That is enough to replace platform event parsing, but **not enough to replace dispatcher semantics**. The safe landing point is:

1. SDK adapter receives and normalizes the platform event.
2. A joelclaw authorization/policy wrapper rejects unauthorized humans and classifies passive vs invoking Slack traffic. ([Discord authorization](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/discord.ts#L186-L203), [Telegram authorization](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/telegram.ts#L1080-L1099), [Slack classification](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/slack.ts#L710-L897))
3. The wrapper converts the SDK message/action/reaction into contract-v2 inbound events with platform IDs, raw anchor IDs, audit lineage, and the existing channel-context injection. ([gateway channel contract](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/types.ts#L1-L47), [daemon enqueue boundary](../../../packages/gateway/src/daemon.ts#L4580-L4650))
4. `command-queue` remains the only path into the Pi session. SDK `concurrency` should be `concurrent` or a shallow burst guard so it does not create a second invisible queue before the durable queue. ([durable enqueue](../../../packages/gateway/src/command-queue.ts#L520-L711), [durable drain](../../../packages/gateway/src/command-queue.ts#L858-L1228))

**Self-wake-loop verdict:** the SDK’s `isMe` defense is real and centralized, but it is necessary rather than sufficient. Keep current platform bot filters, exact Joel allowlists, and the gateway’s source/policy filters during shadow and after cutover. ([core self filter](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2067), [current Discord bot + user filters](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/discord.ts#L186-L203), [current Slack bot + user routing](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/slack.ts#L710-L897))

## Hosting on flagg

### Process model

The packages are plain ESM with `node >=20`; they are not coupled to Next.js. Webhook examples use Web `Request`/`Response`, while Telegram polling, Slack Socket Mode, and Discord Gateway all run in a long-lived process. Bun already runs the gateway and implements the required Node/Web APIs, but this must be proven by a scratch integration before package adoption. ([core manifest](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/package.json#L1-L30), [existing Bun gateway script](../../../packages/gateway/package.json#L1-L10))

**Recommended topology: embed one Chat instance in the existing gateway process supervised by `com.joel.gateway`, not a second LaunchAgent.** The existing LaunchAgent already runs `packages/gateway/src/daemon.ts`; co-hosting keeps one transport owner, one authorization boundary, and one shutdown/health surface. A second process would contend for Telegram polling and could load-balance rather than mirror Slack Socket Mode events. (`file:/Users/joel/Library/LaunchAgents/com.joel.gateway.plist`, `file:/Users/joel/.joelclaw/scripts/gateway-start.sh:1-16`, [Slack connection behavior](https://docs.slack.dev/apis/events-api/using-socket-mode/), [Telegram runtime modes](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L330-L586))

### Transport per adapter

| Adapter | Best flagg transport | LaunchAgent viability | Caveat |
|---|---|---|---|
| Discord | Persistent Gateway WebSocket, direct processing; use HTTP Interactions only if we deliberately keep a public/tailnet webhook endpoint for commands/buttons. | **Viable with wrapper.** `discord.js` reconnects during the duration, but the public SDK API is a duration-bound `startGatewayListener`, not an indefinite actor. The wrapper must capture the `waitUntil` promise, abort on SIGTERM, and restart the listener before/after duration expiry. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L1961-L2108)) | Do not configure the Discord Interactions Endpoint and also expect the same interactions through Gateway; Discord picks one interaction path. Regular messages/reactions always need Gateway. ([docs](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/README.md#architecture-http-interactions-vs-gateway)) |
| Telegram | `mode: "polling"` inside the resident process. | **Viable.** `initialize()` starts polling; SIGTERM must call `telegram.stopPolling()` because `Chat.shutdown()` will not. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L330-L515)) | Polling and webhook are mutually exclusive, and only one poll owner may consume the bot token. Preserve the current ownership/lease rule or make the embedded adapter the sole owner. ([adapter docs](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/README.md#notes), [current lease](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/telegram.ts#L1798-L1810)) |
| Slack | `mode: "socket"` inside the resident process. | **Best fit.** `initialize()` starts the Socket Mode client and `disconnect()` cleanly stops it. ([source](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L835-L870), [socket lifecycle](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L1902-L2220)) | Slack refreshes Socket Mode connections every few hours; feed lifecycle/error signals into joelclaw channel-health. ([Slack docs](https://docs.slack.dev/apis/events-api/using-socket-mode/), [channel health](../../../packages/gateway/src/channel-health.ts#L1-L390)) |

### Shadowing rule

Outbound can shadow by deliberately sending through old and SDK paths and comparing returned IDs/journal rows. Inbound cannot be shadowed by blindly starting duplicate poll/socket/gateway consumers. Mirror each raw event from the current owner into the SDK normalization path inside the same process, compare normalized contract-v2 events, and only then transfer listener ownership. ([current daemon composition root](../../../packages/gateway/src/daemon.ts#L4651-L4890), [SDK webhook normalization entry](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L399-L455))

## Auth and provisioning

No token value was read or copied into this asset.

### Discord

Exact SDK inputs are `DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN`, `DISCORD_PUBLIC_KEY`, and `DISCORD_APPLICATION_ID`; optional `DISCORD_MENTION_ROLE_IDS` controls role mentions. The resident listener requests Guilds, GuildMessages, MessageContent, DirectMessages, GuildMessageReactions, and DirectMessageReactions intents. The app invite needs `bot` + `applications.commands` plus send/read-history/thread/reaction/file permissions used by the chosen surface, and the slash commands still need registration. ([constructor](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L114-L198), [Gateway intents](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/src/index.ts#L2006-L2020), [setup](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-discord/README.md#discord-application-setup), [current registration](../../../packages/gateway/src/discord-ui/slash-commands/register.ts#L1-L109))

**Reuse verdict: yes, reuse the existing joelclaw Discord application/bot identity.** The gateway config already knows `discord_bot_token` and `discord_allowed_user_id`; the live start script currently blanks both, so the identity exists but Discord is disabled. Add the existing app’s public key/application ID to the secret/config surface rather than creating another bot. Keep `DISCORD_ALLOWED_USER_ID` as joelclaw authorization because Chat SDK does not consume it. ([gateway config surface](../../../packages/cli/src/commands/gateway.ts#L709-L729), `file:/Users/joel/.joelclaw/scripts/gateway-start.sh:73-78`)

### Telegram

Exact SDK input is `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`. `TELEGRAM_BOT_USERNAME` is optional because `getMe` discovers identity. Polling needs no new platform secret; webhook mode should add `TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET_TOKEN` and register that same secret in `setWebhook`. Whether polling or webhook, ensure updates include messages, callback queries, and `message_reaction` or reaction-in will never fire. ([constructor/init](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L297-L376), [webhook verification](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L403-L458), [update dispatch](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/src/index.ts#L587-L634))

**Reuse verdict: yes, reuse the current Telegram bot.** The LaunchAgent script already leases `telegram_bot_token`, and the gateway keeps Joel’s chat ID separately as `TELEGRAM_USER_ID`. Feed that ID into the authorization/target wrapper; it is not Chat SDK auth. ([gateway config surface](../../../packages/cli/src/commands/gateway.ts#L687-L708), `file:/Users/joel/.joelclaw/scripts/gateway-start.sh:73-74`)

### Slack

For the recommended single-workspace Socket Mode setup, provide the existing app’s bot token (`SLACK_BOT_TOKEN`, `xoxb-…`) and app-level token (`SLACK_APP_TOKEN`, `xapp-…`) with `connections:write`. Configure interactivity and slash commands, and subscribe to `app_mention`, `message.channels`, `message.groups`, `message.im`, `message.mpim`, `reaction_added`, and `reaction_removed`; add assistant/app events only if we use those surfaces. Baseline bot scopes are `app_mentions:read`, channel/group/DM history+read scopes, `chat:write`, `reactions:read`, `reactions:write`, and `users:read`. Add `assistant:write` only if we choose Assistants/agent streaming features. Webhook mode would use the bot token plus `SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET` instead of the app token. ([Socket Mode auth](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/README.md#socket-mode), [manifest/scopes](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/README.md#slack-app-setup), [event dispatch](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L1413-L1485), [factory validation](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/src/index.ts#L5402-L5485))

**Reuse verdict: yes.** `startSlackChannel` leases `slack_bot_token` and `slack_app_token`, and live gateway readback showed Socket Mode connected and healthy. Keep `SLACK_ALLOWED_USER_ID`, important-channel policy, and Reply Grants outside the SDK. The current `slack_user_token` is used to derive Joel’s ID/default DM in the start script; Chat SDK itself does not require a user token for bot operation. ([current token lease](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/slack.ts#L1072-L1115), `command: joelclaw gateway status`, `file:/Users/joel/.joelclaw/scripts/gateway-start.sh:80-89`)

## Gateway-semantics mapping

| Current guarantee | SDK equivalent | Landing |
|---|---|---|
| Platform send/edit/delete/reaction primitives | `Thread`, `SentMessage`, adapter post/edit/delete/add/remove reaction methods. ([common types](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/types.ts#L908-L989), [sent message](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/types.ts#L1468-L1513)) | **Replace hand-rolled transport mechanics.** |
| `telegram-outbound-policy` | None. ([policy source](../../../packages/gateway/src/telegram-outbound-policy.ts#L1-L344)) | **Keep before SDK send.** Journal suppress/digest/investigate without calling adapter. |
| `error-emission-budget` | Logger only; no budget/window summary. ([SDK logger config](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/types.ts#L54-L150), [budget](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/error-emission-budget.ts#L1-L118)) | **Keep wrapper.** Feed SDK errors into it where they become operator messages. |
| Exact `message-journal` + flow lookup + fail-open outbox | Thread history/transcripts store conversational content, but not transport lineage or delivery state. ([SDK transcripts](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/types.ts#L2500-L2628), [journal](../../../packages/gateway/src/message-journal.ts#L53-L192)) | **Keep.** Record requested before send and confirmed/failed after SDK result; persist platform message ID for reaction correlation. |
| `channel-health` snapshots, alerts, mute/heal policy | Adapter lifecycle/logs are platform-specific. ([health model](../../../packages/gateway/src/channel-health.ts#L1-L390)) | **Keep.** Add thin adapter probes/actors. Slack maps cleanly; Discord/Telegram need lifecycle wrappers. |
| Durable `command-queue` priority, dedupe, batching, supersession, abort, replay | Core offers message-ID dedupe and handler concurrency only. ([core](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2455), [queue](../../../packages/gateway/src/command-queue.ts#L520-L1228)) | **Keep as sole dispatcher queue.** Avoid double queuing. |
| `operator-relay` signal classification/digest/suppression | None; SDK does platform events, not operator attention policy. ([relay](../../../packages/gateway/src/operator-relay.ts#L1-L465)) | **Keep before durable enqueue/outbound.** |
| Outbound routing + reply/thread anchors | SDK has typed adapter-prefixed thread IDs and proactive thread handles. ([thread API](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L1839-L1898), [current router](../../../packages/gateway/src/outbound/router.ts#L1-L257)) | **Evolve into contract v2.** Platform must be explicit; preserve source attribution, `replyTo`, audit, target, buttons/card, and receipt. |
| Discord UI cards/MCQ/slash handlers | Portable cards/actions cover much, Discord Components v2 covers more, but Discord modals are absent and current specialized flows carry gateway semantics. ([Discord features](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official/discord.mdx#L11-L45), [current UI exports](../../../packages/gateway/src/discord-ui/index.ts#L1-L15)) | **Migrate renderer-by-renderer.** Keep command behavior and callback state; replace Discord.js payload construction where SDK parity is proven. |
| Slack Reply Grants/passive intel | None. ([current Slack policy](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/slack.ts#L710-L1016)) | **Keep.** SDK emits normalized messages/reactions into this policy. |
| Telegram callback→flow correlation | SDK emits action/reaction with platform message ID but does not know joelclaw `flowId`. ([SDK action types](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/types.ts#L2046-L2099), [flow index](../../../packages/gateway/src/message-journal.ts#L151-L192)) | **Keep lookup index.** Populate it from SDK send result. |

## Stability and maintenance verdict

### Release cadence

The four target packages are `4.34.0`, but the monorepo is extremely young and fast-moving: their changelogs contain 49 core/Slack releases, 45 Discord releases, and 25 Telegram releases, all within major `4`. Synchronized version releases landed on [June 16](https://github.com/vercel/chat/commit/2a553aa948e0605d5a93f4c30994ccca72a495f0), [July 1](https://github.com/vercel/chat/commit/6f18930cf340ed1338b3b96020e65bab1a6d64b3), [July 7](https://github.com/vercel/chat/commit/b1940d237463cb9feca7d41382cce87d27ac66fa), and [July 13](https://github.com/vercel/chat/commit/f84b5911e758ee5d57e1736a376fe292962cec36). The large GitHub “releases” number is mostly synchronized package tags, not years of one stable product. ([release page](https://github.com/vercel/chat/releases))

### Breaking-change behavior

There has not been another major-version bump in these changelogs, and API renames generally keep deprecated aliases. But behavior changes are shipping in minors: Telegram changed parse mode in 4.27, thread-history names changed in 4.28, Slack’s typed client name changed in 4.29, Telegram commands arrived in 4.31, and Slack DM threading changed under `agent_view` in 4.34. ([4.27 Telegram behavior change](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/CHANGELOG.md#L112-L165), [4.28 compatibility rename](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/CHANGELOG.md#L101-L142), [4.29 Slack rename](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/CHANGELOG.md#L121-L147), [4.34 Slack DM model](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/CHANGELOG.md#L1-L20))

Recent fixes show why shadowing matters: `maxConcurrent` was documented but ignored until 4.27; Slack Socket Mode retries were acknowledged and dropped until 4.33; the old 5-minute dedupe TTL could allow a Slack retry through until 4.33; and Telegram Markdown/truncation could cause reliable 400s until 4.27. ([concurrency fix](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/CHANGELOG.md#L210-L219), [Socket retry loss](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-slack/CHANGELOG.md#L69-L78), [dedupe fix](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/CHANGELOG.md#L39-L54), [Telegram send fix](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/adapter-telegram/CHANGELOG.md#L112-L165))

### Tracker health

At research time GitHub reported **17 open / 114 closed issues** and **13 open / 575 closed pull requests**. That is healthy maintainer throughput, not a stability guarantee; [Slack top-level DM streaming issue #503](https://github.com/vercel/chat/issues/503) is a concrete recent edge case. ([open issues query](https://github.com/vercel/chat/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20state%3Aopen), [closed issues query](https://github.com/vercel/chat/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20state%3Aclosed), [open PR query](https://github.com/vercel/chat/pulls?q=is%3Apr%20state%3Aopen), [closed PR query](https://github.com/vercel/chat/pulls?q=is%3Apr%20state%3Aclosed))

### Honest answer

- **Stable enough to spike and shadow:** yes. The adapter surface is broad, source quality is serious, tests are substantial, and maintainers are fixing real platform edge cases quickly. ([adapter tests](https://github.com/vercel/chat/tree/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages), [recent commits](https://github.com/vercel/chat/commits/main/))
- **Stable enough to delete hand-rolled ingress now:** no. Every target adapter is beta, important delivery/concurrency defects were fixed within the last three versions, and lifecycle semantics are incomplete for a resident Discord+Telegram process. ([beta receipts](https://github.com/vercel/chat/tree/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/apps/docs/content/adapters/official), [lifecycle gaps](#hosting-on-flagg))
- **Best adoption shape:** pin `chat` + all adapter/state packages to the same exact version; wrap behind `@joelclaw/*`; keep one process and one listener owner; preserve joelclaw policy/journal/health/queue; shadow outbound receipts first and mirrored normalized inbound second; require platform-specific canaries before each cutover. ([synchronized package versions](https://github.com/vercel/chat/releases/tag/chat%404.34.0), [hexagonal package rule](../../../AGENTS.md#hexagonal-architecture-adr-0144--mandatory))

## Required canaries before cutover

These are not extra research questions; they are the minimum proof the build steps must produce because source inspection cannot prove live platform behavior:

1. Proactive DM from a cold process on all three adapters, with returned platform ID journaled and read back. ([SDK proactive handles](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L1770-L1898), [journal contract](../../../packages/gateway/src/message-journal.ts#L53-L192))
2. Reaction add/remove on that exact outbound message flows back with platform, actor, thread, message ID, and joelclaw `flowId`. ([SDK reaction event](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/types.ts#L1981-L2030), [flow lookup](../../../packages/gateway/src/message-journal.ts#L151-L192))
3. Bot output never re-enters the dispatcher; a non-Joel human never reaches `command-queue`. ([core self filter](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L2011-L2067), [Discord allowlist](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/discord.ts#L186-L203), [Telegram allowlist](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/telegram.ts#L1080-L1099), [Slack policy](../../../packages/gateway/src/channels/slack.ts#L710-L897))
4. Burst of five inbound messages preserves joelclaw supersession/priority semantics without an SDK default-drop or double-queue loss. ([SDK default](https://github.com/vercel/chat/blob/80def3ab17d2bd06ca630db83ca0e32b2e93e191/packages/chat/src/chat.ts#L291-L380), [joelclaw queue](../../../packages/gateway/src/command-queue.ts#L520-L1228))
5. Kill/restart the LaunchAgent during ingress and during outbound; prove Telegram ownership, Slack reconnect/retry, Discord restart, journal fallback, and unacked replay. ([current replay](../../../packages/gateway/src/command-queue.ts#L1219-L1265), [current health/heal](../../../packages/gateway/src/channel-health.ts#L1-L390), [SDK lifecycle](#transport-per-adapter))
